<H3> <TI>   Questions of Control of Walking Machines </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Questions of Control of Walking Machines </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   Kiev PRIKLADNAYA MEKHANIKA in Russian No. 10, 1993 
(manuscript received 10 Mar. 93) pp. 123-128 </F>

<F P=103> Kiev </F>
<F P=104>  PRIKLADNAYA MEKHANIKA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by V. B. Larin , Institute of Mechanics imeni S,. </F>
P. Timoshenko; Ukrainian Academy of Sciences; Kiev] UDC 62973 
  [Abstract] Development of algorithms of a control system 
for walking machines was examined from positions of optimization 
of periodic controllable systems with variable relations. During 
this, consideration of dynamic processes caused by a change of 
the imposed connections greatly improved the quality of 
algorithms of control and, especially, decreased loadings on 
control mechanisms. Mathematical modelling of the movement of a 
machine with biomechanical mesurements of parameters of human 
walking were presented and discussed. Conclusions of other 
authors concerning this question were discussed. References 47: 
37 Russian 10 Western. 


</TEXT>

